</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxekl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xekl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/20/01 8:49:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mess in my Spellbook</span><hr size=1> My spellbook:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://bit.csc.lsu.edu/~raymond/images/spellbook.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
If you notice I have harvest and gate on the last page.  They never really change once memmed, so they're on page 50.  When I die I just hit /book 50 then mem those 2 spells, then /book 1 to mem my main spells.  First 4 pages are devoted to common spells that I use.  Then all my gate and portal spells.  If you notice the gate spells and portal spells are sort of aligned.  i.e. fay gate and fay portal are both in the same lower left corner.  The gates all overlap with portals.   My lures and other spells, the uncommonly used spells (except when raiding) are pushed further back.  The translocates that require the reagent are on page 48 (/book 48 gets me there fast).  Other rarely used spells or those that are never used are pushed more in the center to the end of the book.<br>
<br>
This setup works great for me and from time to time I make minor changes, but this is pretty much it. <p><center>
